                  <msItem>
                     <p> BERMETON, &amp;o. <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, son of the King, constable of England, warden of East March towards Scotland</persName>
               in pursuance of a grant by him by letters patent to 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Boteler</surname>
                        </persName> of all
               his lands, tenements, &amp;c. in the bishopric <placeName type="diocese" key="place_103020">Durham</placeName>,
                        in the villages of <placeName key="place_108896">Bermeton</placeName>, <placeName key="place_1083324">Bisshopton</placeName>, <placeName key="place_1083486">Newebyggyng</placeName>, <placeName key="place_1083468">Little Staynton</placeName>, and <placeName key="place_1083431">Hedley</placeName> appoints <persName>Sir <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Fulthorp</surname>, kt.</persName>, and 
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Nonwyk</surname>, esq.</persName>, his
               attorneys to deliver seisin of the same. 
               Dated at the castle of <placeName role="date" key="place_1083586">Werkeworth</placeName>, 14 May, <origDate notBefore="1413-03-21" notAfter="1414-03-20">1 Hen. V</origDate>. 
                </p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
